A school fire believed to have broken out in the early hours of the morning when school students were sleeping in a building attached to a mosque near Monrovia, Liberia. Police have told the BBC that they are still looking for bodies in the ruins of the building. Mr George Weah, the president of Liberia has tweeted his condolences to bereaved families.  Officials told AFP news agency that the victims were between 10 and 20 years old. BBC correspondent Jonathan Paye-Layleh reports from the scene that Red Cross ambulances have already taken bodies away from the scene, and there are plans to bury them on Wednesday afternoon. Vanguard Nigeria News. Liberia voted Tuesday in a delayed but peaceful run-off election for a new president, contested by former international footballer George Weah and Vice-President Joseph Boakai. December 26, 2017 In "News" Vote counting was under way in Liberia on Wednesday following a peaceful run-off election for a new president, pitting former international footballer George Weah against Vice-President Joseph Boakai. December 27, 2017 In "News" The UN Mission in Liberia (UNMIL) on Friday, finally concluded a 15-year mission in the one-time war-torn country, describing its operations as a success. March 30, 2018 In "News"